{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "HowTo", "name": "DIY First Birthday Hat for Girls", "image": ["https://www.momsandcrafters.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/first-birthday-hat-final-1-720x540.jpg", "https://www.momsandcrafters.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/first-birthday-hat-final-1-735x983.jpg"], "author": {"@type": "Person", "name": "Menucha @ Moms & Crafters"}, "dateModified": "2022-06-07", "description": "Make a super easy-to-wear first birthday hat using a little felt and some tulle! This DIY project turns a traditional birthday hat into a comfortable headband for your little one.", "prepTime": "PT20M", "totalTime": "PT45M", "supply": [{"@type": "HowToSupply", "name": "Good, thick felt sheet", "url": "https://www.dickblick.com/items/kunin-premium-felt-charcoal-9-x-12/?SSAID=992277&sscid=41k6_qkrtb&utm_source=SAS&utm_medium=affiliates&ref=affiliates"}, {"@type": "HowToSupply", "name": "Tulle ribbon", "url": "https://amzn.to/3Kj5mAy"}, {"@type": "HowToSupply"}], "tool": [{"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "6-7 inch round plate to trace", "url": "https://amzn.to/3xR1JPW"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Ruler", "url": "https://rstyle.me/+U1oBJQQeFfr3X89xmSQ2rg"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Tailor's chalk", "url": "https://rstyle.me/+8vuvqWd9BVVQ-koV8ibL4g"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Fabric scissors", "url": "https://rstyle.me/+ec_J0MQ-ZKlLarCTRCiDPg"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Hot glue gun", "url": "https://amzn.to/3xOJryt"}], "step": [{"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Trace and Cut", "text": "Trace your plate and make a roughly 7 inch circle. Measure a line on the radius of the circle (half the width/diameter). Cut off a bit more than half of the circle."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Form the Cone", "text": "Fold it in half and glue the straight edge together to form a seam. Make sure the cone is in a proportion that you like. When it dries, trim the seam if necessary and turn your hat right side out."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Trim and Decorate", "text": "Trim around the base. Make your pom pom and attach it to the tip of the cone. Optionally, add a tulle border around the base for extra flair."}, {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Final Touches", "text": "Trace a circle a tiny bit smaller than the base of your cone and glue it to the base of your first birthday hat. Attach an elastic to fit around your baby's head and cover it with a smaller piece of felt to hide the elastic seam."}]}